<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-04T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="742" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d742">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2870: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-04T19:00:00-05:00">December 4, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>144. Your 638, December 4, 2 p.m. Do not make an appointment with
                                    Vasconcellos concerning this matter. As soon as any opportunity
                                    presents itself, however, you should, after talking with the
                                    Minister make clear to Vasconcellos the substance of the
                                    Department’s 141 and previous telegrams concerning our policy.
                                    Similar clarification should be made in your discretion to other
                                    officials whenever opportunity and occasion offers.</p>
                                <p>It is almost incomprehensible that any misunderstanding should
                                    still exist in any quarter in Geneva concerning our position,
                                    which has repeatedly been stated in definite and unambiguous
                                    terms.</p>
                                <p>Please keep the Minister informed of any conversations you may
                                    have along these lines.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>